# JWT Configuration Rules

## Secret Keys
- Always use `JWT_ACCESS_SECRET` for access tokens
- Always use `JWT_REFRESH_SECRET` for refresh tokens
- Never use `JWT_SECRET` or other variations

## Default Values
```typescript
// Access token secret
process.env.JWT_ACCESS_SECRET || 'your_jwt_secret_here'

// Refresh token secret
process.env.JWT_REFRESH_SECRET || 'your_refresh_secret_here'
```

## Token Generation
```typescript
// Access token
jwt.sign(payload, process.env.JWT_ACCESS_SECRET || 'your_jwt_secret_here', options);

// Refresh token
jwt.sign(payload, process.env.JWT_REFRESH_SECRET || 'your_refresh_secret_here', options);
```

## Token Verification
```typescript
// Access token
jwt.verify(token, process.env.JWT_ACCESS_SECRET || 'your_jwt_secret_here');

// Refresh token
jwt.verify(token, process.env.JWT_REFRESH_SECRET || 'your_refresh_secret_here');
```

## Environment Variables
Required environment variables in `.env`:
```
JWT_ACCESS_SECRET=your_access_secret_here
JWT_REFRESH_SECRET=your_refresh_secret_here
```

## Test Environment
In test files or setup:
```typescript
process.env.JWT_ACCESS_SECRET = 'test-access-secret';
process.env.JWT_REFRESH_SECRET = 'test-refresh-secret';
```

## Files that must follow these rules:
- `src/utils/auth.ts`
- `src/middleware/auth.ts`
- `src/controllers/authController.ts`
- All test files using JWT 